Xiaomi’s latest offering continues to challenge what’s possible in affordable and innovative technology. The Xiaomi Corporation announced today that the much-anticipated Redmi Note 11 Series will launch in Nigeria on the 9th of February, 2022. Redmi Note 11 Series<br /> As a hugely popular product series with over 240 million units sold worldwide, Redmi Note Series continues the legacy of challenging what is possible. This series of mid-range devices is set to offer superior specs in the realms of camera, display, battery and charging efficiency, providing high-level performance to suit the ever-evolving needs of consumers across the board. Redmi Note 11 Series is the next step in Xiaomi’s global mandate to make innovative technology both accessible and affordable. <img loading="lazy" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Xiaomi.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1656889 lazyload" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Xiaomi.jpg 1280w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Xiaomi-1062x598.jpg 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Xiaomi-640x360.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Xiaomi-320x180.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Xiaomi-278x156.jpg 278w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Xiaomi-556x312.jpg 556w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Xiaomi-515x290.jpg 515w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Xiaomi-1030x580.jpg 1030w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Xiaomi-712x401.jpg 712w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Xiaomi-1424x802.jpg 1424w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Xiaomi-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Introducing the Redmi Note 11 Series is just the beginning of Xiaomi’s 2022 objective to satisfy Xiaomi fans’ appetite for cutting-edge technology and further elevate user experiences. The spirit of the Redmi Note 11 Series also acts as a call-to-action to Xiaomi fans, inspiring them to rise to their everyday challenges and create a better version of themselves. As the year progresses, the company is set to release smartphones and AIoT technologies that enables Nigerians to maximise their lifestyles and make the most of every moment.